//\xa0Perform\xa0input\xa0validation\xa0to\xa0detect\xa0attacks
String\xa0query\xa0=\xa0"SELECT\xa0account_balance\xa0FROM\xa0user_data\xa0WHERE\xa0user_name\xa0=\xa0?\xa0";
PreparedStatement pstmt = connection.prepareStatement( query );
pstmt.setString(\xa01,\xa0custname);
ResultSet\xa0results\xa0=\xa0pstmt.executeQuery(\xa0);
```

#### Safe C\# .NET Prepared Statement Example

In .NET, the creation and execution of the query doesn't change. Just pass the parameters to the query using the `Parameters.Add()` call as shown below.

